## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| Toast notification system not yet implemented from KSA-93 | Medium | Low | Implement simple inline toast as fallback |
| API endpoint may have different response format across variants (Kotlin/Python/Node.js) | Low | Medium | Verify response format is consistent; handle gracefully |
| Concurrent users marking same entry | Low | Low | API is idempotent — marking already-reviewed entry is a no-op |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* The backend API POST /api/kb/entries/{id}/review is already deployed and functional
* The response format returns success (200 OK) with entry data or minimal confirmation
* The ui-tokens.css and ux-components.css provide sufficient styling primitives
* The dashboard page is served from the same origin as the API (no CORS issues)
* Users have appropriate permissions to mark entries as reviewed (no auth check needed at UI level — API handles authorization)

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Category | Requirement | Details |
| Performance | API response time | Mark reviewed action must complete within 500ms |
| Performance | UI responsiveness | Button click to visual feedback < 100ms (loading state) |
| Accessibility | Keyboard navigation | Button must be focusable and activatable via Enter/Space |
| Accessibility | Screen reader | Button must have aria-label “Mark entry {id} as reviewed” |
| Accessibility | Color contrast | Toast notifications must meet WCAG AA contrast ratio |
| Usability | Error recovery | User can retry on failure without page refresh |
| Compatibility | Browser support | Chrome, Firefox, Edge (latest 2 versions) |

